          "email": "wshilong@ddn.com",
          "date": "2014-08-03 11:54:01.000000000",
          "tz": 480
        },
        "subject": "LU-5328 libcfs: fix build warnings without HAVE_LIBREADLINE",
        "message": "LU-5328 libcfs: fix build warnings without HAVE_LIBREADLINE\n\nIf macro HAVE_LIBREADLINE is not defined, we will hit the following\nbuild warnings:\n\nutil/parser.c:286:13: error: ‘noop_int_fn’ defined but not used\n[-Werror=unused-function]\n static void noop_int_fn(int unused) { }\nutil/parser.c:287:13: error: ‘noop_void_fn’ defined but not used\n[-Werror=unused-function]\n static void noop_void_fn(void) { }\n\ncc1: all warnings being treated as errors\nmake[4]: *** [libcfsutil_a-parser.o] Error 1\nmake[4]: Leaving directory `/home/wangsl/lustre-release/libcfs/libcfs'\nmake[3]: *** [all-recursive] Error 1\nmake[3]: Leaving directory `/home/wangsl/lustre-release/libcfs/libcfs'\nmake[2]: *** [all-recursive] Error 1\nmake[2]: Leaving directory `/home/wangsl/lustre-release/libcfs'\nmake[1]: *** [all-recursive] Error 1\nmake[1]: Leaving directory `/home/wangsl/lustre-release'\nmake: *** [all] Error 2\n\nFix these warnings by wrapping function definition into macro.\n\nSigned-off-by: Wang Shilong <wshilong@ddn.com>\nChange-Id: Ibaff9379b9da40d2ed47c02a120142eeb4b376fd\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
